svg.title: Journal of Mammalogy Cover: Pronghorn in Steppe Habitat
svg.desc: American Pronghorn in Steppe Habitat (great plains) that was used on the cover of Journal of Mammalogy issues (numbers) from Volume 1 through 10 (1919 through 1929). The main focus is the right profile of an American Pronghorn with steppe habitat in the background. To the right of the pronghorn’s head are some prairie dogs can be seen, with a herd of pronghorn in the distance and mountains in the far distance. To the left of the pronghorn’s rear end are some tumbleweeds and a few pronghorn in the distance. The original artist was Ernest Thompson Seton. His art has now aged into the public domain. This SVG vector version is by Pipfrosch Press and was created in 2020. It is released under the terms of the Creative Commons BY-SA 4.0 license.
